Description: Client-Server Architecture and What Happens When You Open a Website

1) What is Client-Server Architecture?

The web works on a Client-Server Model.
Client : User device (Mobile, Laptop, Computer)
Server : Powerful computer storing websites
Internet: Medium connecting client and server
Request : Asking for data
Response: Getting data
Real-Time Example:
Customer -> Client (Browser)
Waiter -> Internet
Kitchen -> Server
Food -> Website

2) Steps When You Open a Website:

Step 1: You type URL (example: https://amazon.com)
Step 2: Browser sends request to server through internet.
Step 3: Server responds with files:
- HTML (Structure)
- CSS (Design)
- JavaScript (Functionality)
- JSON (Data)
Step 4: Browser renders and displays the webpage.
